Text.Value: And I you, you delectable vintage.

Text.Value: Dribbles is probably dead.
Interrupting a massacre, Myrkul help me. These three make the art of dance look like ritual sacrifice.

Another Zethino fan? Aren't you just the sweetest thing.

EditorData.NodeContext: excited - thinking of all the money she will make

That is NOT my Dribbles! I WILL REND THAT PESTILENT IMPOSTOR LIMB FROM LIMB.

Text.Value: Find my Dribbles - you won't be disappointed.
We are decades from that. I hoped they could open for Dribbles - not that my star needs the support, but at this rate... who knows?
This whole circus would be dead if not for me. You should have been here.
Ohhh, getting hacked up like that must have been unpleasant - poor dear.

Text.Value: I'll resurrect him - the show must go on, after all! Perhaps I'll make some improvements along the way.

Is this a circus act?
Not now, darling.

When you run a plane-hopping circus of ragtags and ruffians, few things faze you.

Text.Value: Leave.

Normally I'd invite you into my tent for a lovely vintage, but these graceless skellies need my full attention. Enjoy my circus, darling!

Synopsis: Main dialog for the ringmaster - a necromancer lady and the owner of the circus. She has her own tent where she trains dancing skeleton troupe, but after combat with Dribbles she runs to the combat scene and will ask player some questions.
